# CVE-2026-31789 — libcrypto3 / libssl3 (OpenSSL)
# Heap buffer overflow on 32-bit systems from large X.509 certificate.
# NOT exploitable on 64-bit x86_64 (Azure Container Apps runs on amd64).
# Present in nginx:1.28-alpine base image (libcrypto3 3.5.5-r0).
# Fixed in: libcrypto3/libssl3 3.5.6-r0.
# Expected until the nginx:1.28-alpine image is rebuilt with the fix.
CVE-2026-31789
